```
📦 heterogeneous-penalties-at-the-top
├── 📁 data/          — Datasets and data preparation files
├── 📁 codes/         — Replication and extension code
├── 📁 figures/       — Figures used in the paper and presentation
├── 📁 tables/        — Regression tables and outputs
├── 📁 presentation/  — Slides and presentation materials
└── 📁 report/        — Main paper and appendix
```
 
---
 
## Methods
 
| Method | Application |
|--------|-------------|
| Double Post-Lasso | High-dimensional variable selection |
| Causal Forest | Heterogeneous treatment effect estimation |
| Double Machine Learning (DML) | Semiparametric wage gap estimation |
| DML-IRM | Interactive regression model |
| Propensity Score Weighting | Selection correction |
| Cross-Fitting | Sample-splitting for valid inference |
 
---
 
## Data
 
**2016 American Community Survey (ACS)**, restricted to:
- Full-time, year-round employed individuals
- Ages **25 to 65**
- White non-Hispanic women with high educational attainment
 
---
 
## Reference
 
> Bach, P., Chernozhukov, V., Kurz, M. S., & Spindler, M. (2018). *Closing the U.S. Gender Wage Gap Requires Understanding Its Heterogeneity*. arXiv preprint.
